commitmsg: [BuildGetter] Fix uncaught exception, don't close ftp handle
[BatchTester] Give batches uids, remove debug print() statement
[BatchTester] Give skipped builds uids as well
[BatchTester] (de)serialize uids
[BatchTester] Give all builds that reach pending a uid
[BatchTester] Change build note for skipped builds
[BatchTester] Don't raise exceptions if 'lastbuild' is not set
[BenchTester] Create basic indexes in db by default
Fixup copyright/coding headers
[BenchTester] Don't print datapoints to stdout - they're creating epic-sized logs
[BatchTester] Fix typo from refactoring (args -> self.args)
[BatchTester] If should_test() sets a build.note, don't overwrite it
[BatchTester] Add 'requested' and 'processed' to batch data
[BatchTester] Remove obsolete import
[BuildGetter] Remove socket.settimeout() - it conflicts with multiprocessing {http://bugs.python.org/issue6056}
[BatchTester] Various bugfixes and improvements. Works.
[BatchTester] Added. Doesn't quite work.
[EnduranceTest] Add work-around for mozrunner's broken stop()
[BuildGetter] Fix reference-before-assignment
[BenchTester] Bail out if _open_db fails
[BuildGetter] _ftp_check_build_dir() shouldn't raise an exception on directory not found
[BuildGetter] Fix filename calculation for tinderbox builds

[BuildGetter] Share ftp handle as long as possible

So we don't re-open the connection 400 times to queue 200 builds.
[BuildGetter] Catch exceptions looking things up in Hg in get_hg_range
[BuildGetter] Remove superfluous return from __init__

[BuildGetter] Lookup build info on build creation rather than in prepare().

Allows get_revision() and get_buildtime() to work on unprepared builds
[BuildGetter] Fix misuse of _ftp_check_build return type

[BuildGetter] Fix copy-n-paste error

these were supposed to be null'd in the initializer. Oops.
[BuildGetter] Fix TinderboxBuild not having noDL argument on fetch()
[BuildGetter] Return false from prepare instead of exceptions
[BuildGetter] Fix missing member issue
[BuildGetter] Remove get_name, ensure get_revision() works without being prepared (with some overhead)
add_test_results should not return failure if there's no DB

[EnduranceTest] Fix mis-using run_tests return value (it has none).

len(mozmillinst.fails) tells us if anything failed
[BenchTester] Fix typo in table creation
[BenchTester] Properly bail out of sqlite logging if DB operations fail
[BuildGetter] Add get_hg_range()
[EnduranceTest] Mark incomplete tests as unsuccessful in DB
[BenchTester] New column "successful" in test table, for marking partial tests as failed
[EnduranceTest] If the test dies, try to remove junk profile directory
[EnduranceTest] At least attempt to kill mozmill if the test dies
[BuildGetter] Add get_name() and fix some misc bugs from testing
Update comment
Remove --autobuild, add CompileBuild type to BuildGetter() as a replacement
[EnduranceTest] Support --jsbridge_port
[BuildGetter] Extract builds to temp directories to avoid collision
Fix a few dict accesses to use .get() so we don't fail when some options arn't set
Add BuildGetter.py -- utility to grab/build various builds from ftp.m.o
[Endurance] Remove useless 'mem' node (there's no other data atm)

Ensure the DB is opened when any tests are run

So that even tests that fail or produce no data add a test record

[EnduranceTest] Remove jsbridge hack, fixed in jsbridge 2.4.9

Bug 722707
[EnduranceTest] Join node names with / instead of .

[EnduranceTest] Parse iteration number from [i:1 e:9] string

Since the new enduranceCheckpoint stuff means iterations
might not come out in order
[EnduranceTest] Treat endurance_results as a dict

[EnduranceTest] Also handle non-standard enduranceCheckpoint callback

Used by the areweslimyet stuff

[Endurance] Get all MemoryReporters, not just explicit/resident

Older builds don't have explicit/resident, and this also
gets us much more data in general
[Endurance] Remove --mozmill-tests parameter, just accept direct path of a test to run
Fix build() logic ensuring checkout-> build has run
Missing )
Python doesn't do while var = value; syntax
Implement --autobuild-log
Import mercurial.commands explicitly to make older Hg versions happy
Remove obsolete py3k warning (this file can't be run directly anymore)
Add license header
Initial commit

Merge pull request #1 from EricRahm/mozmill-2.0

Add mozmill-2.0 support to MozBenchtester

Add mozmill-2.0 support to MozBenchtester

This is based on the previous work of @Nephyrin. mozmill-2.0 lets us remove a fair amount of hackery related to jsbridge and profile cleanup.
[BuildGetter] Wrong timestamp for TinderboxBuild
[EnduranceTest] Ensure the profile directory is always cleaned up before returning
[BuildGetter] make get_buildtime not throw for un-prepared ftpbuilds
[BuildGetter] Fix nightly builds
[EnduranceTest] Update for new DB format

[BenchTester] Add 'meta' column to benchtester_data and add_test_results

So data can now hold number:string pairs. This is going to be used on
AWSY to not have to have "Iteration 1/<huge datapoint>" and
"Iteration 2/<same huge datapoint>" cause 400% overhead in the
benchtester_datapoints table
[BenchTester] Remove trailing whitespace
[BuildGetter] Fix get_valid for FTPBuild
[BatchTester] build.get_valid -> build.build.get_valid
[BatchTester] Use build.get_valid() to determine a build should continue
[BuildGetter] Add build.get_valid() instead of throwing exceptions on prepare()

[BuildGetter] Don't lookup CompileBuild revisions in Hg

Redundant with pushlog. Also use pushlog commit for everything

[BuildGetter] Check for failures when calling pushlog_lookup()

Don't throw uncaught exceptions, instead make sure all builds without
full info simply cannot be prepare'd

[EnduranceTest] Call stop_runner() instead of stop() to avoid errors

Passing fatal=True makes .cleanup() throw errors, but is necessary to
avoid hangs. We don't need mozmill to cleanup the profile, so just call
stop_runner() directly

[EnduranceTest] Pass fatal=True to mozmill.stop()

We don't need to re-use the instance, so there's no need to wait on a "proper"
shutdown.
[BuildGetter] FTPBuild supports 'try:rev' shorthand for paths
[BatchTester] Actually append series to created build objects
[BuildGetter] Account for branches with paths (integration/mozilla-inbound)
[BuildGetter] Change default branch to mozilla-inbound
[BatchTester] (de)serialize branch name for tinderbox builds
[BuildGetter] Avoid hard-coding mozilla-central
[BuildGetter] Make sure timestamp is always numeric in TinderboxBuild.__init__

[BatchTester/BuildGetter] Use json pushlog to lookup full revision IDs

Removes the need to use hg directly to do so
[BuildGetter] Fix typo
[BuildGetter] Fixup regex
[BuildGetter] Handle non-mozilla-central branches for FTPBuild
[BuildGetter] Fix missing variable error
[BatchTester] Use 'firstbuild' not 'path' (like all other batch requests)
[BuildGetter] Fix syntax typo
[BatchTester] Add series field to batch builds
[BuildGetter,BatchTester] Add support for raw FTP path builds
[BuildGetter,BatchTester] Track tinderbox timestamp for tinderbox builds
[EnduranceTest] Fix syntax errors from previous push
[Endurance] If tester sends back units, prefix them to datapoint

[BenchTester] Bump sqlite timeout to 15m

I saw one timeout at 5m, sqlite + slow disk + 8 tests simultaneously finishing +
cron job reading DB can leave one test waiting more than 5m for its turn to
commit.

[BenchTester] use executemany() instead of a loop to insert datapoints

Also adds time info. With this change it takes ~20s to insert 110k datapoints
which is pretty much all i suspect we can expect from sqlite.
Update index to include datapoint_id
Raise sqlite3 timeout to 5m
Update database schema
[BenchTester] Change non-fatal error to a warning
[BenchTester] Use insert/update instead of replace for differing build timestamps
[BuildGetter] Fix TinderboxBuild.get_buildtime() throwing if the build didn't lookup properly
[BenchTester] If build timestamps differ, warn and update instead of failing
[BuildGetter] Small cleanups
[BuildGetter] Lookup proper push dates from pushlog json instead of patchwork of educated guesses
[BatchTester] The arg is --force, not --retest
Add comments to BatchBuild members
[BatchTester.py] Add --force to force retest builds
[BenchTester] Raise sqlite3 timeout to 60s
[BatchTester] Fix tester.log not being used
[BatchTester] fix CnP issue
[BatchTester] Restore CompileBuilds with the right logfile in deserialize()
[BatchTester] Fix failed builds overwriting builds['failed'] and not having a finished timestamp
[BuildGetter] Turn an accidental debug print into a proper _stat()

[BuildGetter] Recurse through the find-merged-timestamp logic in CompileBuild

And add some more exception handling

[BatchTester] No longer quit in batchmode.

Though this lets us do more cleanup, we lose our recently failed builds
and such, and re-importing these is more work than I care to do
[BuildGetter] Fix CnP error from last commit

[BuildGetter] Very explicitly sort things in revset query

Mercurial changed both these sort behaviors in different builds, meaning
this query was broken on albus :(

[BuildGetter] Ensure logfile is always closed and None'd

If we try to re-pickle the build in a subprocess with the logfile open,
pickle vomits
[BuildGetter] Python can't int("1.2") :(
[BuildGetter] Timestamps should always be integers for database reasons
[BuildGetter] Close logfiles when done with them in CompileBuild
[BuildGetter] Yet another mercurial compatibility fix

[BuildGetter] use limit(x, 1) for revset query

As the second parameter isn't optional in older mercurial versions
[BuildGetter] Use limit() instead of first() for maximal compatibility

[BatchTester] --mode compile rather than --mode build

For consistency

[BatchTester] Exit in batch mode when we're done with work instead of just resetting

This lets the script that loops the tester do its cleanup, and does a much
more complete reset. We still wait until we've done at least one thing.

[BatchTester] Bail out of build is missing it's timestamp (can happen with CompileBuilds)

Also fix some wierd pull logic. CompileBuild's constructor doesn't pull, so
we pull, but that means we don't need CompileBuild to ever pull...
That needs to be fixed.
[BuildGetter] For compilebuild's, get the effective merge date and use that as the timestamp

[EnduranceTest] Move up the deletion of the profile directory so it's deleted when we bail out

Also remove a bunch of trailing spaces
[BatchTester] TinderboxBuild -> BuildGetter.TinderboxBuild

[BatchTester & BuildGetter] Change get_tinderbox_builds to list_tinderbox_builds

Makes it more useful for cronjobs on albus

[BatchTester] Ensure build.finished is always set on skipped builds

And remove a bunch of trailing spaces
[EnduranceTest] Clarify comment for stop/wait hax
[EnduranceTest] Work around mozrunner's broken wait() function, too!
[EnduranceTest] Add exception info to test run failed message
[BatchTester] Fix another batch culling issue
[BatchTester] Cleanup an error message
[BuildGetter] Return False in _ftp_get, check return in users
[BatchTester] Cleanup handling of resume dummy batch
[BatchTester] Fix reference to old variable name in batches pruning

[BatchTester] When recovering builds with --status-resume, create a dummy batch entry

So the status page can be updated to show what the tester is doing while its restarting
[BatchTester] Keep failed builds for 3 days rather than 5
[BatchTester] self.tick was in the wrong class's __init__. Oops.
[BatchTester] Trim complete/failed/skipped lists more often

[BatchTester] Clean up error messages a little more

The build failed: and encountered exception: prefixes are just spam.
If its in the failed list, it failed. If the exception message starts with
<Exception.SomeException>: Of course it hit an exception.

[BatchTester] Shorten an error message so the end result is less redundant

Because this doesn't look good:
"Task returned error Test worker encountered an exception:"

[EnduranceTest] Add a default for --jsbridge_port

24242 is the default jsbridge port

[EnduranceTest] Return false for run_test if errors were encountered

and print them in a self.error()

[EnduranceTest] Fix the runner.stop() hack to actually be callable

It wasn't failing before because the test harness was cleaning up mozmill anyway. Ugh.
[EnduranceTest] Include exception message when complaining about mozmill.stop() failing
[BatchTester] Fix ret not being initialized in test_build, causing it to return False
[BenchTester] Save all warnings/errors in tester.warnings and tester.errors lists
[BatchTester] Count builds filtered for being already in queue in the "Queued x builds" note
[BatchTester] Fix build_is_queued not being a member function
[BatchTester] Fix stupid typos from previous commit
[BatchTester] Repair the skipping of builds already in queue
[BuildGetter] Print message when reconnecting to FTP
